Bower.
    - Bower is the Automation Tool for UI Application Development.

    - Bower is the Automation Tool Provided By NodeJS Platform.

    - Bower used to Download the Required Dependencies to Develop Web Applications.

bower components.
-
    we have Two Bower Components.

    1. bower.json
    2. .bowerrc

bower.json
-
       - This Component used to mention the Required Resources to develop web application.

Ex.

{
    "name":"nareshit",
    "dependencies":{
        "angular":"~1.6.0",
        "bootstrap":"~3.3.6"
    }
}


.bowerrc
-
    - this component used to indicate the "path to resources" are "downloading by using bower".

{
    "directory":"bower_components"
}


> bower install  (This Command Used to Execute / Install the Bower Components)


Bower will give the Following Path for Angular Framework.

"bower_components/ angular / angular.min.js"


index.html
-

<html>
    //Logic Goes Here
    <script src="bower_components/angular/angular.min.js"></script>
</html>


Installing the Dependencies Dynamically.
-
> bower install bootstrap --save


Uninstalling the Dependencies.
-
> bower uninstall angular


list of Dependencies Installed.
-
> bower list










